Simon Ince (62) is set to receive it as the oldest person to swim from Simon's Town to Rooi Els, crossing False Bay. #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - A new Guinness World Record will soon be awarded in South Africa. Simon Ince (62) is set to receive it as the oldest person to swim from Simon's Town to Rooi Els, crossing False Bay. Ince took on the almost eleven-hour long swim of just over 32-kilometres on Sunday. "I looked at records five years ago and I realised if I was gonna do this in five years I'd be old and I thought I'd just go for a record," he said.